You said:
how to make the content center

ChatGPT said:

To make content center in Tailwind CSS, it depends on what you want to center:

  • Text

  • Image

  • Entire column

  • Entire page

  • Both vertically and horizontally

Here are the correct methods

1. Center an image (your case)

Use:

html
className="mx-auto"

Example:

html
<img
  src="/images/book.png"
  className="h-20 w-20 object-contain mx-auto"
/>

This centers image horizontally

2. Center text

Use:

html
className="text-center"

Example:

html
<h3 className="text-center font-semibold">
  Book Appointments
</h3>

3. Center everything inside a column (BEST for your feature cards)

Use flex + items-center:

html
className="flex flex-col items-center"

Example:

html
<div className="flex flex-col items-center">
  <img src="/images/book.png" className="h-20 w-20 object-contain" />

  <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold mt-3">
    Book Appointments
  </h3>

  <p className="text-gray-500 text-center">
    Schedule your appointment easily
  </p>
</div>

Image centered
Text centered
Everything aligned perfectly

4. Center entire section horizontally

Use:

html
className="flex justify-center"

5. Center vertically AND horizontally (full center)

Use:

html
className="flex items-center justify-center min-h-screen"

BEST solution for your Healthcare 3-column layout

Use this structure:

html
<div className="flex flex-col items-center text-center">

  <img
    src="/images/book.png"
    className="h-20 w-20 object-contain mb-4"
  />

  <h3 className="text-xl font-semibold">
    Book Appointments
  </h3>

  <p className="text-gray-500">
    Easily schedule your visit
  </p>

</div>

Most important classes summary

PurposeClass
Center imagemx-auto
Center texttext-center
Center column contentflex flex-col items-center
Center horizontallyjustify-center
Center verticallyitems-center

If you want, I can give the exact Tailwind layout for your 3 features section matching your website screenshot perfectly.

ChatGPT said:

In Tailwind CSS, sizes increase based on the spacing scale. After 56, the next sizes are:

Tailwind classSize (rem)Size (pixels)
h-56 / w-5614rem224px
h-60 / w-6015rem240px
h-64 / w-6416rem256px
h-72 / w-7218rem288px
h-80 / w-8020rem320px
h-96 / w-9624rem384px

Next size after 56 is:

html
className="h-60 w-60 object-contain mx-auto"

Size = 240px 240px

Best recommended for your healthcare cards

Use:

html
className="h-64 w-64 object-contain mx-auto"

Size = 256px 256px Perfect large size

Final professional recommendation

html
className="h-56 w-56 md:h-64 md:w-64 object-contain mx-auto"

Mobile: 224px
Desktop: 256px Ideal

If image still looks small after h-64, then the issue is transparent padding inside the image, not Tailwind size.
